About Project:

Project Name: Customized DBMS Using C++ Language.
Author: Yogeshwar Prakash Chaudhari.
File Name: Final.cpp

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//
// Project Overview:
//
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Customized DBMS Using C++ is a mini database management system built entirely using C++ and STL (Standard Template Library).
It demonstrates how core DBMS operations like insertion, deletion, searching, displaying, and backup/restore can be implemented using object-oriented programming 
and file handling concepts in C++.
The project acts as a simplified version of a relational database system where employee records are stored, managed, and persisted using binary files (config.dat).

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//
// Features:
//
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

1) Insert Records
Add new employee records dynamically with unique auto-generated IDs.

2) Display All Records
View all stored employee data in a formatted table.

3) Search Functionality
Find employees by ID or Name.

4) Delete Records
Remove an employee record by specifying their ID.

5) Backup and Restore
Automatically save and load data to/from a binary file (config.dat) to ensure persistence across sessions.

6) Menu-Driven Interface
Simple, console-based interface for user interaction.

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//
// Project Structure:
//
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Customized-DBMS-Using-C++
│
├── Final.cpp          # Main source file containing all class definitions and logic
├── config.dat         # Binary file used for backup & restore (auto-created)
└── README.md          # Project documentation

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//
// Technologies Used:
//
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

C++ (Object-Oriented Programming)
STL – list container
File Handling (Binary I/O)
Basic Console UI

Classes Overview
Employee

Handles employee data such as:
ID (auto-incremented)
Name
Age
Address
Salary

Includes methods for:
Writing and reading binary backups
Displaying employee details

MarvellousDBMS
Acts as the main DBMS engine.

Implements:
Insert, Display, Search, Delete operations
Backup and Restore functionality
Menu-driven user interface

